<p><lb/>M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Morcom. the Registers wife <lb/><rs type="address" xml:id="address1" key="PLACE968" resp="#mhawkins">in Blandford, in Comitatu Dorset</rs>. <lb/><unclear cert="medium" reason="binding"><choice><orig>I</orig><reg>J</reg></choice></unclear>ugulatur a famulo. seu amanuensi. <lb/>Sam: Collins. In Lecto. absente Marito. <lb/>Sept: 22. h. 11. 45. p. m. <choice><orig>d ☾</orig><reg>die Lunæ</reg><reg type="gloss">Monday</reg></choice>.</p>
</div>
<div xml:id="translation001" xml:lang="en" decls="#translation">
<p>Mrs Morcom the registrar’s wife in Blandford in the county of Dorset was murdered in [her] bed by a servant or secretary, Sam Collins, the husband being absent, Monday 22 September at 11.45pm.</p>
</div>
